01:03.832 --> 01:06.831
It doesn't count
if it's not in our house!

01:06.832 --> 01:08.631
Put me down!

01:08.632 --> 01:10.671
It's ours for a week.
It is, isn't it?

01:10.672 --> 01:13.391
We could dine out!
Stay in.

01:13.392 --> 01:15.271
We could go to the theatre!
Go to bed.

01:15.272 --> 01:18.351
I'm gonna have trouble
getting you outside, aren't I?

01:18.352 --> 01:21.311
We... we did it.

01:21.312 --> 01:23.191
We did.

01:23.192 --> 01:24.752
We have a lifetime of this.

01:28.232 --> 01:32.112
Mmm! Ti amo cosi tanto.

01:33.232 --> 01:34.752
Ti adoro.

01:36.472 --> 01:38.512
Mmm!

01:39.472 --> 01:41.991
What a beautiful wedding.

01:41.992 --> 01:44.551
I'm glad you were part of the day.

01:44.552 --> 01:46.631
As am I, darling.

01:46.632 --> 01:50.951
I was surprised to see Jack
replace Amo as best man.

01:50.952 --> 01:53.391
Well, he and Gino have become close.

01:53.392 --> 01:57.551
So close? The Italians tend towards
sentiment in such matters.

01:57.552 --> 01:59.872
The new generation.

02:01.392 --> 02:03.031
Perhaps.

02:03.032 --> 02:04.792
Perhaps not.

02:06.592 --> 02:08.072
See you in the morning.

02:12.592 --> 02:15.991
You sure?
She was hinting at something.

02:15.992 --> 02:18.271
You had fairly spurious reasons
to be up there,

02:18.272 --> 02:20.591
and we were radiating
a certain glow.

02:20.592 --> 02:23.471
Yeah. You would just think
that we're happy.

02:23.472 --> 02:26.191
I've always refused
to name Anna's father

02:26.192 --> 02:27.911
and there we three were.

02:27.912 --> 02:29.711
She's not blind.

02:29.712 --> 02:31.391
So, what do we do?

02:31.392 --> 02:32.991
No stress, you said.

02:32.992 --> 02:36.391
Which is greater - having it
confirmed or having to wonder?

02:36.392 --> 02:39.392
For her? Being lied to.

02:41.472 --> 02:46.111
For a part well played. I added
something extra for discretion.

02:46.112 --> 02:49.591
I won't be here to gossip anyway.
I'm on the next ship to London.

02:49.592 --> 02:52.591
I can see you in the next
tawdry West End farce.

02:52.592 --> 02:55.351
Well, consider yourself
a benefactor to the arts.

02:55.352 --> 02:59.071
I'll drop you near the station
and then I'll head to Ash Park.

02:59.072 --> 03:04.111
And you'll, what, hurry hot
and distressed to the front door?

03:04.112 --> 03:05.832
Exactly.

03:07.352 --> 03:09.591
Satisfy my curiosity.

03:09.592 --> 03:11.471
Why this obsession?

03:11.472 --> 03:13.472
George seems rather dull to me.

03:15.312 --> 03:17.471
I was 15 when we first met.

03:17.472 --> 03:21.072
He was the most gorgeous thing
I'd ever seen.

03:23.592 --> 03:25.391
Elaine would never
have stood a chance

03:25.392 --> 03:27.351
if I'd been a few years older.

03:27.352 --> 03:30.831
I'd have had the property,
his heirs...

03:30.832 --> 03:32.632
..his affection.

03:35.752 --> 03:38.831
She rubbed my nose in it
whenever possible.

03:38.832 --> 03:41.471
I swore I'd have him one day.

03:41.472 --> 03:43.831
You missed your vocation.

03:43.832 --> 03:47.832
Your Lady Macbeth
would be spectacular.

